text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia tenuispica is a tree or shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to an area in the Kimberley region of Western Australia.The open branched spreading tree or shrub typically grows to a height of 1.5 to 5 metres (5 to 16 ft). It blooms from May to July producing yellow flowers.
